Website - Bhuvan-MGNREGA (Mahatma Gandhi National Rural Employment Guarantee Act)
Website URL - https://bhuvan-app2.nrsc.gov.in/mgnrega/mgnrega_phase2.php#
Website Content Details- 
Bhuvan-MGNREGA is a geospatial application developed by the National Remote Sensing Centre (NRSC) of the Indian Space Research Organisation (ISRO) to track the implementation of the Mahatma Gandhi National Rural Employment Guarantee Act (MGNREGA) in India. The application uses satellite imagery and other geospatial data to provide a visual representation of MGNREGA works across the country.

Bhuvan-MGNREGA has a number of features that make it a valuable tool for monitoring MGNREGA. These features include:

A map viewer that allows users to view MGNREGA works at different scales and levels of detail.
A layer manager that allows users to customize the map view by adding or removing layers of data.
A search function that allows users to find specific MGNREGA works.
A statistics dashboard that provides information on the progress of MGNREGA works across the country.
Bhuvan-MGNREGA is a powerful tool that can be used by a variety of stakeholders to monitor the implementation of MGNREGA. These stakeholders include:

Government officials who are responsible for implementing MGNREGA.
NGOs that work with rural communities to implement MGNREGA.
Researchers who study the impact of MGNREGA.
The general public who want to learn more about MGNREGA.
Bhuvan-MGNREGA is available to the public for free. To access the application, users can visit the Bhuvan website or download the Bhuvan app for Android or iOS.

Here are some specific examples of how Bhuvan-MGNREGA can be used:

Government officials can use Bhuvan-MGNREGA to track the progress of MGNREGA works in their districts or states. They can use the application to identify areas where works are behind schedule or where there are quality concerns.
NGOs can use Bhuvan-MGNREGA to monitor the implementation of MGNREGA in the communities they work with. They can use the application to identify communities that are not benefiting from MGNREGA or where there are labor rights violations.
Researchers can use Bhuvan-MGNREGA to study the impact of MGNREGA on rural development. They can use the application to track changes in infrastructure, land use, and livelihoods over time.
The general public can use Bhuvan-MGNREGA to learn more about MGNREGA and how it is being implemented in their area. They can use the application to see where MGNREGA works are taking place and to learn about the benefits of MGNREGA.
Bhuvan-MGNREGA is a valuable tool that can help to improve the implementation of MGNREGA and ensure that it is reaching the intended beneficiaries.
